<TITLE> BHF to decide ban on Abahani's Jahid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 10 (bdnews24.com)  The league committee has recommended a ban on Abahani goalkeeper Jahid Hossain from the upcoming Club Cup Hockey tournament after finding him guilty of taking money from duo clubs during the player transfers. The committee also decided to fine the young goalkeeper Tk 10,000. The decision was taken at the league committee meeting Thursday. "We have decided to ban Jahid from the club cup hockey tournament as we found him guilty of receiving money from both Usha Krira Chakra and Abahani during the player transfers," league committee secretary Ehtesham Sultan told bdnews24.com after the meeting. "The meeting also decided that Jahid would have to regret to Usha and return the money he took from the club," said Sultan. Sultan said that they sent their decisions to the hockey federation that would take the final decision about Jahid. On April 3, joint champion Abahani roped in Jahid shoving Usha officials, who claimed that Jahid promised them to play for Usha and took Tk 75,000 on April 2 along with nine other players. bdn
